1053			// it is necessary to have the argument to already be a `value<N>`, since template argument deduction and implicit
1054			// type conversion are mutually exclusive. In these contexts, we use dump_sigspec_rhs() to emit an explicit
1055			// type conversion, but only if the expression needs it.
1056			bool is_complex = dump_sigspec(sig, /*is_lhs=*/false, for_debug);
1057			if (is_complex)
